Delicious! Not as hard as it seems, and everybody loved it, even the picky ones! I don't like the drizzled chocolate and nuts on top, I thought it took away from the golden brown color of the phyllo, but to each their own.

Rating: 4
I started making this with the leftover phyllo dough whenever I make spanakopita - huge hit. Have tried with the dried cherries as suggested in the reviews, but found it a bit too sweet. LOVE it with the dates. Also took the advice of Troy from VA and used his syrup recipe - much eaiser, and very tasty. I skip the chocolate sauce and whipped cream and go for the more typical, simple, Greek presentation. Fantastic!

Rating: 4
This is always a hit when I make it. It's NOT dry but in fact very juicy and moist even after a day or two. It's very flexible and you can add/subtract ingredients depending on your allergies/dislikes/etc. This is a keeper for sure.

