I made this as is & it was fantastic! Took it to work for a Christmas port & stilton party we host at the pub every year & had to print out several copies of the recipe.

Rating: 3
It was a big hit! Slightly dry so next time I will make a bit more syrup and put some honey and lemon in it.

Rating: 3
I made this recipe for a Greek-themed dinner club meal and wanted to try something other than just the traditional baklava. It turned out so well! It was very easy to put together and I took the recommendation of another cook to substitute the dates for dried cherries (cut down on the sugar if the cherries are sweetened). I added for presentation a cherry red wine sauce and a sour cream/whipping cream mixture. I drizzled the sauces across triangled baklava pieces for added color and flavor and it looked great. Everyone at the dinner club loved it!

Rating: 3
This recipe was ALMOST perfect. I skiped the water and sugar mixture for a more traditional mixture of honey (1/4 cup), light corn syrup (1/4 cup) enough water just to thin it out a bit (maybe 1/8 cup) oh and a tbsp of molasses.

Rating: 4
I made this recipe as is and it was fabulous. The proportions are great, it's not too chocolaty or too sticky. Everyone loved it.

